llm-rag-project
    backend
        rag.py (remove api key)
        main.py (FastAPI)
        requirements.txt
    
    uploads
    .env (contains OpenAI key)
    Dockerfile (to implement containerization)
    Jenkins (to implement pipeline/configurations)
    .gitignore
    .dockerignore (docker configuration)

Step 1:
    do changes in requirements.txt

    uvicorn[standard]
    python-dotenv

Step 2:
    create .env file

Step 3:
    modify rag.py file

Step 4:
    create .gitignore file

Step 5:
    create .dockerignore file

Step 6:
    create Dockerfile

Step 7:
    Create Jenkinsfile (pipeline)
        Stage 1: Checkout appln from GitHub
        Stage 2: Build Docker Image (Dockerfile)
        Stage 3: Push Docker Image to Docker Hug (Optional)
        Stage 4: Deploy Docker Image to EC2

Step 8:
    push code to repo

Step 9:
    Create EC2 instance
    Note: 20GB+ SSD required
    Open below ports
        8000 (Uvicorn)
        8080 (Jenkins)
        3000 (ReactJS)

Step 10:
    Assign elastic IP (permanent IP address)
    Ex: 13.63.68.207

Step 11:
    Open the below ports

Step 12:
    Update Ubuntu (refresh)
        > sudo apt update -y

Step 13:
    install Java
        > Jenkins installation depending on Java
        > https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/linux/
        > java --version

Step 14:
    > Install Jenkins
    > https://www.jenkins.io/doc/book/installing/linux/
    > java --version

Step 15:
    > install docker
    > sudo apt install docker.io -y
    > docker --version

Step 16:
    > enable permissions
    > sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu
    > sudo usermod -aG jenkins ubuntu
    > sudo usermod -aG docker jenkins

Step 17:
    > restart both jenkins & docker
    > sudo systemctl restart jenkins
    > sudo systemctl restart docker

Step 18:
    > connect to jenkins
    > http://13.63.68.207:8080/
    > password: sudo cat <command>

Step 19:
    > install below plugins
        > Git server
        > Docker & Docker pipeline
        > SSH, SSH server & SSH agent
        > AWS Credentials

Step 20:
    > install docker desktop
    > https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/?utm_source=chatgpt.com
    > create account and set username & password

Step 21:
    > configure Credentials in Jenkins
        > OPENAI_API_KEY
        > EC2_HOST (ubuntu@<ip-address>)
        > ec2-ssh-key (SSH Username w/ key)
        > dockerhub-creds (Username with password)

Step 22:
    > create pipeline
    > llm-rag-pipeline






